n = 1\ngitbutler:agentlog-index:v1:branch:<branch-key> = set<session-key/turn-key>\ngitbutler:agentlog-index:v1:review:<review-key> = set<session-key/turn-key>\ngitbutler:agentlog-index:v1:change:<change-id> = set<session-key/turn-key>\n```\n\nThe index value includes both the session key and turn key so an index lookup can\nresolve directly to the owning session without scanning session turn lists.\nBranch and review index key material should be safe for GitMeta keys; hashing\n  branch names, relative file paths, PR identifiers, change ids, commit ids, and\n  commit file lists; what extra controls are needed before exposing a selected\n  web view outside normal repository access?\n- Snapshot size cap: path lists use a cap of 256 entries, plus `file_count` and\n  `files_truncated`.\n- Index rebuild/versioning: use versioned index namespaces. No rebuild/delete\n  command in v1; readers verify candidates against turn detail and ignore old\n  namespaces after future version bumps.\n- Stack model: use a shared GitButler workspace/head-info API that supports both\n  GitButler and plain Git modes; do not add an agentlog-specific plain-Git model\n  unless the shared API proves insufficient.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:06:43.874Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}